label.value: larval abdominal 1 A31k neuron

value.value: Any larval A31k neuron (FBbt:00111665) that has its soma located in some cell body rind of larval abdominal 1 neuromere (FBbt:00051990).

label.value: larval T23a neuron

value.value: Larval thoracic interneuron that is part of lineage 23 (Zwart et al., 2016). Its soma is located laterally, it has dendritic arborizations dorsomedially and a branch crossing the midline forming presynapses (Zwart et al., 2016).

label.value: larval metathoracic T23a neuron

value.value: Any larval T23a neuron (FBbt:00048709) that has its soma located in some cell body rind of larval metathoracic neuromere (FBbt:00051989).

label.value: larval thoracic ladder-1 neuron

value.value: Larval interneuron of the mesothoracic neuromere that is part of lineage 0 (Jovanic et al., 2019). Its soma is located medially and its neurites extend anteriorly and posteriorly either side of the midline (Jovanic et al., 2019). It receives input from mechanosensory chordotonal neurons (Jovanic et al., 2019).

definition.value: Appears only to exist in T2 based on images in Jovanic et al. (2019).

label.value: larval Drunken-4 neuron

value.value: Larval ventral nerve cord interneuron of lineage 30 (Jovanic et al., 2019). From a lateral soma, it projects dorsomedially, then ventrally; it arborizes anteriorly and posteriorly close to the midline on the ipsilateral side (Jovanic et al., 2019).

label.value: larval abdominal 1 Drunken-4 neuron

value.value: Larval Drunken-4 neuron with its soma in the abdominal 1 neuromere (Jovanic et al., 2019). It outputs onto mechanosensory chordotonal neurons and the Jupiter neurons (Jovanic et al., 2019).

label.value: larval Jupiter neuron

value.value: Larval interneuron with a lateral soma (Jovanic et al., 2019). It extends medially, crossing the midline and projecting anteriorly, reaching the subesophageal ganglion; there are also ipsilateral branches arborizing anteriorly and posteriorly close to the midline (Jovanic et al., 2019). It receives input from mechanosensory chordotonal neurons and Drunken-4 neurons and outputs onto recliner neurons (Jovanic et al., 2019).

definition.value: Appears only to only be one of these on each side based on images in Jovanic et al. (2019), but looks like A1 in paper and A2 in catmaid data.

label.value: larval recliner neuron

value.value: Larval projection neuron of the mesothoracic neuromere that is part of lineage 8 (Jovanic et al., 2019). Its soma is located laterally and it extends medially, before sending branches anteriorly and posteriorly on either side of the midline (Jovanic et al., 2019). It receives input from Jupiter neurons and its contralateral anterior branch projects to the brain (Jovanic et al., 2019).

definition.value: Appears only to exist in T2 based on images in Jovanic et al. (2019).
